, both collected by E.L. Sleeper (probably in 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34700" box="[295,354,151,175]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="9" pageNumber="45">CAS</collectionCode>
). Elsewhere in 
<collectingCountry box="[526,611,151,175]" name="Mexico" pageId="9" pageNumber="45">Mexico</collectingCountry>
it is known only from near Monterrey, Nuevo León (
<bibRefCitation author="Westcott" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" refString="Westcott, R. L. &amp; Hespenheide, H. A. (2006) The description of a new species of Agrilus Curtis, with distributional records, and taxonomic and biological notes for Agrilinae and Trachyinae (Coleoptera: Buprestidae) of Mexico and Central America. Zootaxa, 1367, 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="2006">
Westcott &amp; Hespenheide 
<number box="[218,279,188,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In the 
<collectingCountry box="[368,418,188,212]" name="United States of America" pageId="9" pageNumber="45">U.S.</collectingCountry>
it is widespread in the western states (but not the Pacific Northwest) and occurs from Kansas to Texas. No host records from Baja California are available and only adult hosts, 
<taxonomicName box="[1107,1365,224,248]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Gutierrezia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="californica">
<emphasis box="[1107,1365,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="45">Gutierrezia californica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC.) Torr. &amp; A. Gray (
<taxonomicName box="[343,469,260,284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[490,719,260,284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Prosopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glandulosa">
<emphasis box="[490,719,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="45">Prosopis glandulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[773,867,261,284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[773,867,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="45">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. — the latter two surely being incidental resting places, the first likely a larval host—were provided in 
<bibRefCitation box="[789,1023,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" refString="Nelson, G. H., Walters, G. C., Jr., Haines, R. D. &amp; Bellamy, C. L. (2008). A catalog and bibliography of the Buprestoidea of America North of Mexico. The Coleopterists Society, Special Publication No. 4, iv + 1 - 274." type="book chapter">
Nelson et al. (
<number box="[954,1016,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hetz" box="[1156,1436,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" refString="Hetz, M. W. &amp; Werner, F. G. (1979) Insects associated with roots of some rangeland Compositae in southern Arizona. Southwestern Entomologist, 4, 285 - 288." type="journal article" year="1979">
Hetz and Werner (
<number box="[1369,1427,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName box="[220,511,332,356]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Gutierrezia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microcephala">
<emphasis box="[220,511,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="45">Gutierrezia microcephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC.) A. Gray and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Greene) S.F. Blake" authorityName="(Greene) S.F. Blake" box="[745,1265,332,356]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Haplopappus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuisectus">
<emphasis box="[745,1030,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="45">Haplopappus tenuisectus</emphasis>
(Greene) S.F. Blake
</taxonomicName>
(now 
<taxonomicName authority="Greene" authorityName="Greene" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Isocoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuisecta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="45">Isocoma tenuisecta</emphasis>
Greene
</taxonomicName>
), both 
<taxonomicName box="[432,558,368,392]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
, as larval hosts.
